        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 6:59PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 657 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Van Buren SP, or 8 miles southwest of South Haven, moving northeast
at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Winds to 30 mph with possible funnel clouds

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

Locations impacted include...
Saugatuck...           Burnips...             Moline...
South Haven...         Overisel...            Castle Park...
Dorr...                Pullman...             Fennville...
Van Buren SP...        Ganges...              Douglas...
Green Lake...          Hamilton...            South Haven Area Reg...
Lacota...              Glenn...               Saugatuck Dunes SP...
Holland...             Hopkins...
</description>
        <instruction>Conditions are favorable for the development of weak, brief funnel
clouds. Theis type of funnel cloud is harmless, but on rare occasions
they can briefly touch down, producing wind gusts over 50 mph. If a
funnel cloud is spotted move indoors and report your sighting to the
National Weather Service.</instruction>
